<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,439]" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,317,226,252]" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is somewhat similar to species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[875,1001,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Neurigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[875,1001,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Neurigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated from the latter by the metallic green mesonotum and elongated male cercus. In species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[1074,1203,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Neurigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1074,1203,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Neurigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the mesonotum is mainly yellow, at most with metallic green spots, and the male cercus is short and round (
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. M." box="[1266,1423,301,327]" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" pagination="561 - 604" refId="ref4221" refString="Naglis, S. M. (2002) Revision of the Neotropical Neurigoninae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) IV: Viridigona gen. nov. Studia dipterologica, 9 (2), 561 - 604." type="journal article" year="2002">Naglis 2002</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Chen &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Wang, Yang &amp; Grootaert" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[151,382,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Viridigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhangae">
<emphasis box="[151,382,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Viridigona zhangae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents a new Palearctic record for the genus. 
<taxonomicName authority="Naglis" authorityName="Naglis" authorityYear="2003" box="[974,1185,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Viridigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[974,1099,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">Viridigona</emphasis>
Naglis
</taxonomicName>
is now distributed in the Neotropical, Nearctic and Palaearctic regions with 29 known species. Only one species of this genus is currently known from 
<collectingCountry box="[415,489,413,439]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="60">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
